I've been playing this game since release and it never gets old.  The endless mode, which is basically 50% of what is on offer, is awesome.  You get persistent levelling for your character as well which means you can equip better weapons and mods for single and mp (rifles, jump pack, stim packs etc).  The other half of the game is just pure creation mode like in Minecraft where you get unlimited resources and you can build anything then upload your creation online where people can play it in co-op and pvp (in a future update!).  As well as the features that we will be getting in the next patch I would also like to see the races from Block Fortress War represented in some way, rather than just the Goblocks all the time.  Maybe have these as "Elite" waves in the single mp co-op.  For example you get an Elite wave of Zomblocks at Wave 5, then an Elite wave of Blockoids at wave 10 and so on .  Maybe even a boss wave every 20 waves where we are attacked by a Hero unit and their honour guard?  Just a suggestion or two :)

replyContent: Hey there. Once you take a screenshot, it should appear next to your map when loading the game. They are required if you are going to upload a sandbox map for everyone to see. They're not actually stored on your device anywhere (they're pretty low res so our server doesn't get bogged down)
